    "instruction": "From the kernel variable metric_with_anomaly (per-point records and precomputed per-group p95/p5), compute a compact candidate table per (cmdb_id, kpi_name) restricted to the incident window already used. For each group compute: total_point_count, anomaly_count, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, p95, p5, max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window, upward_breach = (max_value - p95)/max(1e-9,p95), downward_breach = (p5 - min_value)/max(1e-9,p5), and max_breach = max(upward_breach, downward_breach). Also compute longest consecutive-anomaly-run length within the window for that group (i.e., the longest contiguous sequence where points were flagged anomalous). Keep the full per-point anomaly table in kernel, but return a compact table of groups that satisfy: anomaly_count >= 3 AND longest_consecutive_run >= 3 AND max_breach > 0.5. Return the top 20 groups sorted by max_breach descending with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, total_point_count, anomaly_count, longest_consecutive_run, earliest_anomaly_timestamp, p95, p5, max_value, min_value, upward_breach, downward_breach, max_breach. Also return the total number of groups that passed these filters. Do not print raw per-point rows."}

